\caption{\small Poincare section plots at the plane $z=0$ with $E=0.976$, $L=4.2$ and $\alpha=2\times 10^{-4}$, without any special relativistic correction. Variation of Kerr parameter: (a) $a=0.0$, (b) $a=0.3$ and (c) $a=0.8$.}
\label{fig1}
\end{figure*}
First of all we investigated the variation of the Poincare section taken at $z=0$, i.e. at equatorial plane, with variation of $E$, the energy of the test particle, other parameters viz. $L$ and $a$ of the system remaining fixed  (not shown here). It was observed qualitatively that the degree of chaos increases with increasing value of $E$, consistent with the earlier findings of some authors. This will be quantitatively shown later in this section.
\begin{figure*}
 \begin{tabular*}{1.0\linewidth}{ccc}
 \includegraphics[width=5cm]{fig14.eps} &
